item.title: CVE-2023-32790|2023-10-03T12:40:23.607Z -- nxlog -- nxlog%20manager
item.description: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability in NXLog Manager 5.6.5633 version. This vulnerability allows an attacker to inject a malicious JavaScript payload into the 'Full Name' field during a user edit, due to improper sanitization of the input parameter.
